cs.LG, cs.CR, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.DS

This paper focuses on improving model robustness against various types of attacks, including backdoor attacks, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a new training process and evaluates different machine learning models, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
